{"title": "Homilies on Hebrews", "description": "Let us then stretch our mind towards Heaven, let us be held fast by that desire, let us \r\nclothe ourselves with spiritual fire, let us gird ourselves with its flame. No man who bears \r\nflame fears those who meet him; be it wild beast, be it man, be it snares innumerable, so \r\nlong as he is armed with fire, all things stand out of his way, all things retire. The flame is \r\nintolerable, the fire cannot be endured, it consumes all. \r\nWith this fire let us clothe ourselves, offering up glory to our Lord Jesus Christ, with \r\nwhom to the Father, together with the Holy Ghost, be glory, might, honor, now and ever \r\nand world without end.  Amen. <br>\r\nThanks be to God. (Summary from Homily 34)", "duration": 57429, "language": "English", "authors": [{"id": "2129", "name": "St. John Chrysostom"}], "coverArt": "https://archive.org/download/homilies_on_hebrews_2204_librivox/homilies_hebrews_2204.jpg", "copyright_year": "1889", "genres": ["Christianity - Commentary"], "supporters": [{"role": "Read by", "name": "A LibriVox Volunteer"}, {"role": "Book Coordinator", "name": "A LibriVox Volunteer"}, {"role": "Meta Coordinator", "name": "Ann Boulais"}, {"role": "Proof Listener", "name": "Ann Boulais"}], "sections": [{"section": 0, "title": "The Argument", "readers": [8368], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/homilies_on_hebrews_2204_librivox/homiliesonhebrews_00_chrysostom_64kb.mp3", "duration": 864}, {"section": 1, "title": "Homily 1 Heb 1:1-2", "readers": [8368], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/homilies_on_hebrews_2204_librivox/homiliesonhebrews_01_chrysostom_64kb.mp3", "duration": 1437}, {"section": 2, "title": "Homily 2 Heb 1:3-5", "readers": [8368], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/homilies_on_hebrews_2204_librivox/homiliesonhebrews_02_chrysostom_64kb.mp3", "duration": 1951}, {"section": 3, "title": "Homily 3 Heb 1:6-2:4", "readers": [8368], "path": "https://www.archive.org/download/homilie